You either believe it or you don't. Well, the devil's doing this.

00:43:04.226 --> 00:43:09.165
No, no, no. We bind the devil. You're not able to do this to me.

00:43:09.166 --> 00:43:17.124
I'm a believing believer. I'm not a doubter. I'm an overcomer. I keep on standing.

00:43:17.125 --> 00:43:23.019
Even when the storm winds and the waves keep trying to knock me down, I'm standing on the inside like that clown.

00:43:23.020 --> 00:43:32.631
You punch that clown down, he gets up, he keeps standing up. I refuse to lay down and let the devil rob me.

00:43:32.632 --> 00:43:42.639
I don't want to be a statistic of death. I don't want to be that. I am a victor. I'm an overcomer.

00:43:42.640 --> 00:43:50.626
And if I go by the graveside, if they bury me in there one day, I've got victory.

00:43:50.627 --> 00:43:54.959
Because to be absent from the body is to be present with the Lord.

00:43:54.960 --> 00:43:59.279
Where, death, you've lost your sting. I'm not going to worry about it.

00:43:59.280 --> 00:44:06.843
I've got victory. Does that make sense? So, I try to encourage you all to keep on keeping on today.

00:44:06.844 --> 00:44:11.166
We love you. We pray for you. We believe God has the best for you.

00:44:11.167 --> 00:44:17.439
And we thank you for joining us every single day, keeping your head up with a smile on your face and a song in your heart.

00:44:17.440 --> 00:44:24.000
Remember, Jesus loves you. We love you. Have a blessed day, y'all.

